      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISSION OF JOY (6) looks the one to beat. She ran a good race first up at Bendigo when getting into fourth and should come on nicely from that. She showed ability in two runs last time in and sets up nicely here from the gate. ICE QUAKE (4) made good improvement second up at Moe, chasing home a dominant winner into second. She'll kick up from the inside gate and prove hard to run down. GASOLINE RAINBOW (3) was okay fresh at Donald on heavy going when fifth, beaten six lengths. She showed some ability last time in and can strip fitter here. LYREBIRD LADY (5) has been going well enough in her first campaign and holds an each-way claim while XTRA STYLISH (10) was solid on debut here at big odds and should be right there again.",
